<doc id="450596" wikidata="Q6331542" url="?curid=450596" title="KJNO">
<text>KJNO (630 AM) is a radio station broadcasting a news/talk/sports format. Licensed to Juneau, Alaska, United States, the station serves the Alaska Panhandle area. The station&#x27;s studios are at the Juneau Radio Center, which is home to KINY, KTKU - TAKU 105, KSUP - MIX 106 and KXXJ - 1330/KXJ. 
The station is owned by Alaska Broadcast Communications, and features programming from CBS News Radio, and ESPN Radio. It carries the nation&#x27;s biggest talk radio stars; Rush, Laura Ingraham, Sean Hannity, Glenn Beck, Mark Levin and others. KJNO also has a very popular local talk show - Actionline which airs at 11 each weekday.

