<doc id="450654" wikidata="Q48103755" url="?curid=450654" title="List of towns in Japan">
<text>A town (町; &quot;chō&quot; or &quot;machi&quot;) is a local administrative unit in Japan. It is a local public body along with prefecture (&quot;ken&quot; or other equivalents), city (&quot;shi&quot;), and village (&quot;mura&quot;). Geographically, a town is contained within a district.

The same word (町; &quot;machi&quot; or &quot;chō&quot;) is also used in names of smaller regions, usually a part of a ward in a city. This is a legacy of when smaller towns were formed on the outskirts of a city, only to eventually merge into it.

==Towns==


